INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L052_v21$$, 2027, $$The FY 2026 spend plan amount for Other Procurement, Air Force includes 67,015
 thousand of discretionary and 1,400 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of 68,415.

 PE 0102325F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) - Joint Surveillance System (JSS)
 Funding provides procurement and installation of aging AN/FPS-117 radomes supporting the AEWS JSS.
 The AEWS provides continuous aircraft and cruise missile early warning against possible threats, Specific aircraft data position, detection from low-mid-high-altitude targets, Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) in
 support of Homeland Defense, PACOM, USNORTHCOM, NORAD and FAA missions. Radars are remotely monitored & controlled, Unattended/minimally attended. AEWS Program provides sustainment support
 for AN/FPS-117 Long Range Radar (250 NM range/100k alt) & AN/FPS-124 Short Range Radar (70 NM range/15k alt) systems to maintain the defense command and control for Alaska, Canada and Hawaii.

 PE 0102412F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) - North Warning System (NWS)
 Funding provides replacement of aging AN/FPS-117 and AN/FPS-124 radomes supporting the AEWS NWS.
 The AEWS provides continuous aircraft and cruise missile early warning against possible threats, Specific aircraft data position, detection from low-mid-high-altitude targets, Identification Friend or Foe (IFF) in
 support of Homeland Defense, PACOM, USNORTHCOM, NORAD and FAA missions. Radars are remotely monitored & controlled, Unattended/minimally attended. AEWS Program provides sustainment support
 for AN/FPS-117 Long Range Radar (250 NM range/100k alt) & AN/FPS-124 Short Range Radar (70 NM range/15k alt) systems to maintain the defense command and control for Alaska, Canada and Hawaii.

 PE 0207439F Electronic Warfare Integrated Reprogramming (EWIR)
 DISTRIBUTED MISSION OPERATIONS AND THREAT CHANGE ANALYSIS: New start. Conducted by the 453rd Electronic Warfare Squadron (453 EWS), EWIR provides analytical capabilities and reachback
 support for DoW acquisition , planning and mission execution activities. These capabilities ensure electromagnetic warfare (EW) systems and integrated combat platforms correctly recognize and respond
 to enemy, friendly and noncombatant systems operating within the electromagnetic environment. The effort includes funds used to procure specialized information technology systems used to identify
 electromagnetic spectrum emitter changes that impact combat defensive and electronic warfare systems and to conduct detailed analyses in support of operational mission planning, tactics, techniques and
 procedures (TTP) development, acquisition and test and evaluation. These analyses provide the means to understand the performance of their systems in hostile environments, directly impacting the survivability
 of combat-coded USAF aircraft and aircrews.

