INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_3080_L061$$, 2027, $$The Air Operations Center Weapon System (AOC WS), AN/USQ-163 Falconer, the senior element of the Theater Air Control System, is the weapon system that the Commander, Air Force Forces (COMAFFOR)
 provides the Combined/Joint Force Air Component Commander (C/JFACC) for monitoring, planning, executing and assessing theater-wide air and space operations in support of the air battle campaign to meet
 the Combined/Joint Force Commander's (C/JFC) objectives.

 AOC includes the fielded AOC 10.1 WS and modernized AOC WS. The Air Operations Center (AOC) 10.1 WS is a comprehensive "system of systems" - encompassing computer and network infrastructure,
 software, and radios - that serves as the critical foundation for 24/7 global air operations. Currently, AOC 10.1 provides the sustainment capabilities for infrastructure and baseline applications at 23 on-premise
 AOC locations. This Program Element (PE) funds the modernization of this existing on-premise architecture, enabling the decommissioning of outdated legacy systems, standardizing the AOC enterprise, and
 enhancing performance and interoperability to mitigate vulnerabilities that disrupt operations and impede WS re-accreditation.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0207410F, Air Operations Center Weapon System

 The All Domain Common Platform (ADCP) is an extensible cloud-based Infrastructure and Platform as a Service (IaaS/PaaS) hosting medium built to deliver highly resilient Command and Control (C2) mission
 applications and data to Airmen deployed around the world. ADCP is a warfighting capability that enables on-boarded users to build, deploy and monitor mission applications to the end state of production.
 Having applications operational in various environments ensures data is accessible as it is needed across United States Air Force (USAF) mission sets. The ADCP's collection of technologies, services, and
 tooling enables warfighter outcomes by abstracting away technical complexity and enabling the deployment of products onto its infrastructure.

 The ADCP is the primary path to production for modernized C2 software-intensive systems. Platform customers include the Air Operations Center (AOC), Intelligence Programs, the 309th Software Engineering
 Group, the 350th Spectrum Warfare Group, and others. ADCP is USAF's contributing platform to the DAF Battle Network and Joint All-Domain Command and Control (JADC2), meeting system resiliency
 requirements through the escalating phases of warfare.

 Funding for this exhibit contained in PE 0303248F, All Domain Common Platform (ADCP)

 Efforts within this program align with and depend upon USAF investment in Mission Planning Systems (PE 0208006F), Air Operations Center (PE 0207410F), Flight Operations (PE 0207461F), All Domain
 Common Platform (0303248F), Command and Control Incident Management Emergency Response Application (C2IMERA) (0305836F) and Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) (0604003F) to deliver$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Air Force                                                                                                                Date: April 2026
