 Description:
 In direct support of the Secretary of War's direction to increase readiness across the Department of War, efforts within this Program Element Code (PEC) will be prioritized in alignment with the National Defense
 Authorization Act (NDAA), U.S. Air Force Force Design, Agile Combat Employment (ACE), and the Defense Planning Guidance (DPG).

 This portfolio program provides a wide variety of base support equipment items with worldwide application. Equipment includes, but is not limited to, Aircraft Arresting Systems (AAS), Base Logistics and Support
 Equipment (BLSE), Tools and Industrial Plant Equipment, Cargo Pallet and Net Systems, Base Generator Power Systems, and Deployable Debrief Facilities (DDF). This equipment provides prime support for
 all base missions. Lack of funding for these equipment items limits safe flight operations, aircraft maintenance and testing capabilities, anti-terrorism and security missions, communications capabilities, and the
 ability of Air Force units to meet deployment requirements.

 In direct support of SecWars direction to increase readiness across the DoW, efforts within this PEC will be prioritized based on the National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA), USAF Force Design, Agile
 Combat Employment (ACE), and the Defense Planning Guide (DPG). These efforts will support work and collaboration efforts across the Combat Readiness Directorate in PE's 78051F, 71212F, 72833F,
 64706F, 65827F, 22834F, 52834F, 52844F, 28031F, 41135F and 27521F) -- to increase readiness across the Air Force Enterprise

